  "text": "Although it may appear that we have gained nothing by this notational manipulation, there is a key advantage of expressing the categorical probability in terms of Bregman divergences. In particular, the second step is to parameterize the Bregman divergence by an additional variance parameter. As discussed in Lemma 3.1 of [CITATION_1] , we can introduce another parameter, which we will call η, that scales the variance in an exponential family while fixing the mean. This new distribution may be represented, using the Bregman divergence view, as proportional to exp(−η · KL(w jt , ψ z jt )). As η → ∞, the mean remains fixed while the variance goes to zero, which is precisely what we require to perform small-variance analysis.",
